		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">3.104-8</ph> Criminal and civil penalties, and further administrative remedies.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <p id="d98e13" class="- topic/p ">Criminal and civil penalties, and administrative remedies, may apply to conduct that violates <ph class="- topic/ph ">
					          <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                     format="html"
                     scope="external"
                     class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. Chapter 21</xref>
				        </ph> (see <ph class="- topic/ph ">
					          <xref href="FAR-i1124784.dita#i1124784"
                     base="i1124784"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">3.104-3</xref>
				        </ph>). See <ph class="- topic/ph ">
					          <xref href="FAR-i1080417.dita#i1080417"
                     base="i1080417"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">33.102</xref>
				        </ph>(f) for special rules regarding bid protests. See <ph class="- topic/ph ">
					          <xref href="FAR-i1124936.dita#i1124936"
                     base="i1124936"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">3.104-7</xref>
				        </ph> for administrative remedies relating to contracts.</p>
			      <ol id="d96e40" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d98e44" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            An official who knowingly fails to comply with the requirements of <xref href="FAR-i1124784.dita#i1124784"
                        base="i1124784"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">3.104-3</xref> is subject to the penalties and administrative action set forth in <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 2105</xref>.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d98e59" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            An offeror who engages in employment discussion with an official subject to the restrictions of <xref href="FAR-i1124784.dita#i1124784"
                        base="i1124784"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">3.104-3</xref>, knowing that the official has not complied with <xref href="FAR-i1124784.dita#i1124784"
                        base="i1124784"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">3.104-3</xref>(c)(1), is subject to the criminal, civil, or administrative penalties set forth in subsection 27(e) of the Act.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d98e74" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            An official who refuses to terminate employment discussions (see <xref href="FAR-i1124883.dita#i1124883"
                        base="i1124883"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">3.104-5</xref>) may be subject to agency administrative actions under 5 CFR 2635.604(d) if the official’s disqualification from participation in a particular procurement interferes substantially with the individual’s ability to perform assigned duties.</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
		    </conbody>
